<para id="fs-idm917582192">More than 100 individuals contributed to this resource, including authors and reviewers listed alphabetically, and lead reviewers Rob McDonald and Carol Berkin, who provided input on the entire publication.</para>
<para id="fs-idm209158112">The Gilder Lehrman Institute of American History (<link url="https://www.gilderlehrman.org/">https://www.gilderlehrman.org/</link>) provided editorial review of Units 3–5. Selected lesson plans are included courtesy of George Washington’s Mount Vernon (<link url="https://www.mountvernon.org/">https://www.mountvernon.org/</link>), John F. Kennedy Presidential Library and Museum (<link url="https://www.jfklibrary.org/">https://www.jfklibrary.org/</link>), the LBJ Presidential Library (<link url="http://www.lbjlibrary.org/">http://www.lbjlibrary.org/</link>), the Ronald Reagan Presidential Foundation and Institute (<link url="https://www.reaganfoundation.org/">https://www.reaganfoundation.org/</link>), and TeachRock (<link url="https://teachrock.org/">https://teachrock.org/</link>).</para>
<para id="fs-idm209804640">Bill of Rights Institute contributors include Kirk Higgins, lead editor and author; Tony Williams, editor and author; and Mary Patterson, Mallory Admire, Gennie Westbrook, and Joshua Schmid.</para>
